# Realtime / Socket Rules

## Namespace

- Dispatch namespace: `/dispatch` on API server.
- Event names align with `DispatchEventType` in `@uk-phv/shared-types`.

## Rooms

- `operator:{operatorId}` — dashboard, dispatchers
- `driver:{driverId}` — driver clients (future; web dispatch is primary)
- `dispatcher:{operatorId}` — dispatch-only staff

## Security (production)

- Authenticate socket connections with JWT before `join:*` handlers.
- Validate `operatorId`/`driverId` matches token claims.

## Location Updates

- Driver location: emit `driver:location`, cache in Redis (TTL 300s).
- Throttle client updates to max 1/second.

## Client

- Web: `getDispatchSocket()` + `joinOperatorRoom()`

## Server

- State changes must persist to DB before emitting events.
- Include `correlationId` on all outbound payloads.
